overview
    https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromiumos/docs/+/HEAD/containers_and_vms.md

Terms
termina 	default vm.
vsh		connect to local vm
vmc		crosh command to manually manage custom VM instances via Concierge.
lxc		launch & manage containers


Management
	start in Crosh (Ctrl+Alt+T)
	Start and log in to termina default vm.
	vmc list - shows VMs, termina is defualt.
	vmc start termina - starts and connects to termina
	vmc destroy <vm>

	vsh termina - connect to vm, use lxc


Containers
	vmc create - create containers
		vmc create termina <container name> <image url> <distro version>

	lxc list
		shows containers
	lxc start <container>
		if doesn't work, logout and run 'vmc container termina penguin'

Login to container
	lxc exec arch -- bash - get shell
	lxc console <container> - login to user

Flatpak error 'Can't mount proc on /newroot/proc'
	from termina prompt
		`lxc config set penguin security.nesting true`
		`lxc restart penguin`

Replace default Debian container
	lxc stop --force f37
	lxd stop --force penguin
	lxc rename penguin debian
	lxc rename f37 penguin
	lxc start penguin


lxd
    manage application containers
    https://linuxcontainers.org/lxd/introduction/


image server site
    https://us.images.linuxcontainers.org/

New distro images can be created either with vmc or with lxd
    https://gist.github.com/rstacruz/aeb2273d19e5f5ffbe27a973cb82717f
    https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Chrome_OS_devices/Crostini#Create_the_container

vmc container termina f37  https://us.lxd.images.canonical.com fedora/37

Cros Guest Tools

[copr:copr.fedorainfracloud.org:mbkulik:cros-guest-tools]

Add repo: 

[copr:copr.fedorainfracloud.org:leo:cros-guest-tools]
name=Copr repo for cros-guest-tools owned by leo
baseurl=https://download.copr.fedorainfracloud.org/results/leo/cros-guest-tools/fedora-$releasever-$basearch/
type=rpm-md
skip_if_unavailable=True
gpgcheck=1
gpgkey=https://download.copr.fedorainfracloud.org/results/leo/cros-guest-tools/pubkey.gpg
repo_gpgcheck=0
enabled=1
enabled_metadata=1

 dnf copr enable leo/cros-guest-tools

install cros-guest-tools

